w:cs="Segoe UI Emoji"/></w:rPr><w:t>📋</w:t></w:r><w:r><w:t xml:space="preserve"> COPY AND PASTE THIS PROMPT TO YOUR DASHBOARD TOOL:</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="5C6A9DD3" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="00C30BC2" w:rsidRDefault="00C30BC2" w:rsidP="00C30BC2"/><w:p w14:paraId="0135870A" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="00C30BC2" w:rsidRDefault="00C30BC2" w:rsidP="00C30BC2"><w:r><w:t>**Context:**</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="7D8A46DF" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="00C30BC2" w:rsidRDefault="00C30BC2" w:rsidP="00C30BC2"><w:r><w:t xml:space="preserve">I am providing a dataset named `netflix_titles.csv` containing 6,234 rows of data regarding Netflix movies and TV shows. Please build a multi-page, highly attractive, and interactive dashboard based on the following detailed specifications. </w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="3CCDDAB7" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="00C30BC2" w:rsidRDefault="00C30BC2" w:rsidP="00C30BC2"/><w:p w14:paraId="404C6DAE" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="00C30BC2" w:rsidRDefault="00C30BC2" w:rsidP="00C30BC2"><w:r><w:t>**Data Cleaning &amp; Pre-processing Instructions:**</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="4F1885D3" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="00C30BC2" w:rsidRDefault="00C30BC2" w:rsidP="00C30BC2"><w:r><w:t>Before visualizing, please apply the following transformations to the dataset:</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="7AD2D2C7" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="00C30BC2" w:rsidRDefault="00C30BC2" w:rsidP="00C30BC2"><w:r><w:t>1. **Date Parsing:** Convert the `</w:t></w:r><w:proofErr w:type="spellStart"/><w:r><w:t>date_added</w:t></w:r><w:proofErr w:type="spellEnd"/><w:r><w:t>` column into a proper Date format. Extract a new column called `Year Added` and `Month Added`. (Note: Handle the 11 missing values by ignoring them in time-series charts).</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="04ED286A" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="00C30BC2" w:rsidRDefault="00C30BC2" w:rsidP="00C30BC2"><w:r><w:lastRenderedPageBreak/><w:t>2. **Handle Delimiters:** The columns `country`, `cast`, `director`, and `</w:t></w:r><w:proofErr w:type="spellStart"/><w:r><w:t>listed_in</w:t></w:r><w:proofErr w:type="spellEnd"/><w:r><w:t>` contain comma-separated multiple values (e.g., a movie might have 3 countries listed). Please split these values so that visualizations can count individual entities correctly rather than treating the whole string as one entity.</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="19341166" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="00C30BC2" w:rsidRDefault="00C30BC2" w:rsidP="00C30BC2"><w:r><w:t>3. **Handle Missing Data:** - `director` (1,969 missing) -&gt; label as "Unknown Director"</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="7D8C33F1" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="00C30BC2" w:rsidRDefault="00C30BC2" w:rsidP="00C30BC2"><w:r><w:t xml:space="preserve">   - `cast` (570 missing) -&gt; label as "Unknown Cast"</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="06B1A61B" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="00C30BC2" w:rsidRDefault="00C30BC2" w:rsidP="00C30BC2"><w:r><w:t xml:space="preserve">   - `country` (476 missing) -&gt; label as "Unknown Country"</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="683E0F88" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="00C30BC2" w:rsidRDefault="00C30BC2" w:rsidP="00C30BC2"><w:r><w:t>4. **Duration Splitting:** Separate the `duration` column into two logical metrics based on the `type` column:</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="2FE6B750" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="00C30BC2" w:rsidRDefault="00C30BC2" w:rsidP="00C30BC2"><w:r><w:t xml:space="preserve">   - For `type = 'Movie'`, extract the numerical value as `Movie Duration (Minutes)`.</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="411348E9" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="00C30BC2" w:rsidRDefault="00C30BC2" w:rsidP="00C30BC2"><w:r><w:t xml:space="preserve">   - For `type = 'TV Show'`, extract the numerical value as `TV Show Duration (Seasons)`.</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="1BE0EC1D" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="00C30BC2" w:rsidRDefault="00C30BC2" w:rsidP="00C30BC2"/><w:p w14:paraId="1ECEC35E" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="00C30BC2" w:rsidRDefault="00C30BC2" w:rsidP="00C30BC2"><w:r><w:t>---</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="7D29B4C7" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="00C30BC2" w:rsidRDefault="00C30BC2" w:rsidP="00C30BC2"/><w:p w14:paraId="44092902" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="00C30BC2" w:rsidRDefault="00C30BC2" w:rsidP="00C30BC2"><w:r><w:t xml:space="preserve">#### </w:t></w:r><w:r><w:rPr><w:rFonts w:ascii="Segoe UI Emoji" w:hAnsi="Segoe UI Emoji" w:cs="Segoe UI Emoji"/></w:rPr><w:t>📊</w:t></w:r><w:r><w:t xml:space="preserve"> DASHBOARD PAGE 1: Executive Overview &amp; Growth Trends</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="2E770F2A" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="00C30BC2" w:rsidRDefault="00C30BC2" w:rsidP="00C30BC2"><w:r><w:t xml:space="preserve">**Goal:** Provide a high-level summary of the Netflix </w:t></w:r><w:proofErr w:type="spellStart"/><w:r><w:t>catalog</w:t></w:r><w:proofErr w:type="spellEnd"/><w:r><w:t xml:space="preserve"> and how it has grown over time.</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="288D8524" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="00C30BC2" w:rsidRDefault="00C30BC2" w:rsidP="00C30BC2"/><w:p w14:paraId="58398979" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="00C30BC2" w:rsidRDefault="00C30BC2" w:rsidP="00C30BC2"><w:r><w:t>* **Global Filters (Apply to all charts):** `Type` (Movie / TV Show), `Release Year` (Slider/Range), `Age Rating` (Dropdown).</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="325BC72B" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="00C30BC2" w:rsidRDefault="00C30BC2" w:rsidP="00C30BC2"><w:r><w:t>* **Scorecards / KPIs (Top Row):**</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="05F478CB" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="00C30BC2" w:rsidRDefault="00C30BC2" w:rsidP="00C30BC2"><w:r><w:t xml:space="preserve">    * **Total Titles:** Count distinct `</w:t></w:r><w:proofErr w:type="spellStart"/><w:r><w:t>show_id</w:t></w:r><w:proofErr w:type="spellEnd"/><w:r><w:t>`.</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="0ECAB1C1" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="00C30BC2" w:rsidRDefault="00C30BC2" w:rsidP="00C30BC2"><w:r><w:t xml:space="preserve">    * **Total Movies:** Count where `type` = 'Movie'.</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="111200D3" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="00C30BC2" w:rsidRDefault="00C30BC2" w:rsidP="00C30BC2"><w:r><w:t xml:space="preserve">    * **Total TV Shows:** Count where `type` = 'TV Show'.</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="7AB64B9B" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="00C30BC2" w:rsidRDefault="00C30BC2" w:rsidP="00C30BC2"><w:r><w:t xml:space="preserve">    * **Total Unique Countries:** Distinct count of separated `country` values.</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="3E7F78E9" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="00C30BC2" w:rsidRDefault="00C30BC2" w:rsidP="00C30BC2"><w:r><w:t xml:space="preserve">    * **Total Unique Genres:** Distinct count of separated `</w:t></w:r><w:proofErr w:type="spellStart"/><w:r><w:t>listed_in</w:t></w:r><w:proofErr w:type="spellEnd"/><w:r><w:t>` values.</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="3B4E695F" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="00C30BC2" w:rsidRDefault="00C30BC2" w:rsidP="00C30BC2"><w:r><w:t>* **Visualizations:**</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="4A2D3C79" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="00C30BC2" w:rsidRDefault="00C30BC2" w:rsidP="00C30BC2"><w:r><w:t xml:space="preserve">    1.  **Content Split (Donut Chart):** % of Movies vs. % of TV Shows. *Make it visually striking with Netflix brand </w:t></w:r><w:proofErr w:type="spellStart"/><w:r><w:t>colors</w:t></w:r><w:proofErr w:type="spellEnd"/><w:r><w:t xml:space="preserve"> (Red/Black/Dark Grey).*</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="4475DB6D" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="00C30BC2" w:rsidRDefault="00C30BC2" w:rsidP="00C30BC2"><w:r><w:lastRenderedPageBreak/><w:t xml:space="preserve">    2.  **Content Added Over Time (Area Chart or Line Chart):** X-axis = `Year Added` (from `</w:t></w:r><w:proofErr w:type="spellStart"/><w:r><w:t>date_added</w:t></w:r><w:proofErr w:type="spellEnd"/><w:r><w:t>`), Y-axis = Count of titles. Use two lines/areas to separate 'Movie' and 'TV Show'.</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="786FCCE5" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="00C30BC2" w:rsidRDefault="00C30BC2" w:rsidP="00C30BC2"><w:r><w:t xml:space="preserve">    3.  **Release Year vs. Platform Addition (Scatter Plot):** X-axis = `</w:t></w:r><w:proofErr w:type="spellStart"/><w:r><w:t>release_year</w:t></w:r><w:proofErr w:type="spellEnd"/><w:r><w:t>`, Y-axis = `Year Added`. This will show how much classic/old content Netflix acquires versus brand-new releases.</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="74146766" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="00C30BC2" w:rsidRDefault="00C30BC2" w:rsidP="00C30BC2"/><w:p w14:paraId="4DCF97C9" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="00C30BC2" w:rsidRDefault="00C30BC2" w:rsidP="00C30BC2"><w:r><w:t xml:space="preserve">#### </w:t></w:r><w:r><w:rPr><w:rFonts w:ascii="Segoe UI Emoji" w:hAnsi="Segoe UI Emoji" w:cs="Segoe UI Emoji"/></w:rPr><w:t>🌍</w:t></w:r><w:r><w:t xml:space="preserve"> DASHBOARD PAGE 2: Geographic &amp; Audience Analysis</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="2FFECADE" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="00C30BC2" w:rsidRDefault="00C30BC2" w:rsidP="00C30BC2"><w:r><w:t>**Goal:** Understand where the content is coming from and who it is meant for.</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="5CB9801D" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="00C30BC2" w:rsidRDefault="00C30BC2" w:rsidP="00C30BC2"/><w:p w14:paraId="5374ADBA" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="00C30BC2" w:rsidRDefault="00C30BC2" w:rsidP="00C30BC2"><w:r><w:t>* **Visualizations:**</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="3E39A691" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="00C30BC2" w:rsidRDefault="00C30BC2" w:rsidP="00C30BC2"><w:r><w:t xml:space="preserve">    1.  **Global Footprint (Choropleth Map):** A world map </w:t></w:r><w:proofErr w:type="spellStart"/><w:r><w:t>colored</w:t></w:r><w:proofErr w:type="spellEnd"/><w:r><w:t xml:space="preserve"> by the count of titles produced in each `country`. (Ensure comma-separated countries are split so co-productions count for both).</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="44B7D507" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="00C30BC2" w:rsidRDefault="00C30BC2" w:rsidP="00C30BC2"><w:r><w:t xml:space="preserve">    2.  **Top 10 Content-Producing Countries (Horizontal Bar Chart):** Y-axis = `country`, X-axis = Count of Titles. Add a stacked element to show the split of Movies vs. TV shows per country.</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="5B744AE7" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="00C30BC2" w:rsidRDefault="00C30BC2" w:rsidP="00C30BC2"><w:r><w:t xml:space="preserve">    3.  **Target Audience / Rating Distribution (Column Chart):** X-axis = `rating` (e.g., TV-MA, TV-14, PG-13), Y-axis = Count of titles. Sort by volume. </w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="176A6633" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="00C30BC2" w:rsidRDefault="00C30BC2" w:rsidP="00C30BC2"><w:r><w:t xml:space="preserve">    4.  **Rating by Type (100% Stacked Bar Chart):** Show how ratings differ between Movies and TV Shows (e.g., are TV shows generally rated more mature than movies?).</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="67DF63AE" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="00C30BC2" w:rsidRDefault="00C30BC2" w:rsidP="00C30BC2"/><w:p w14:paraId="7FFFEA0A" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="00C30BC2" w:rsidRDefault="00C30BC2" w:rsidP="00C30BC2"><w:r><w:t xml:space="preserve">#### </w:t></w:r><w:r><w:rPr><w:rFonts w:ascii="Segoe UI Emoji" w:hAnsi="Segoe UI Emoji" w:cs="Segoe UI Emoji"/></w:rPr><w:t>🎬</w:t></w:r><w:r><w:t xml:space="preserve"> DASHBOARD PAGE 3: Content Deep-Dive (Genres, Duration &amp; Talent)</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="17C28E0D" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="00C30BC2" w:rsidRDefault="00C30BC2" w:rsidP="00C30BC2"><w:r><w:t xml:space="preserve">**Goal:** </w:t></w:r><w:proofErr w:type="spellStart"/><w:r><w:t>Analyze</w:t></w:r><w:proofErr w:type="spellEnd"/><w:r><w:t xml:space="preserve"> the actual content types, durations, and the people behind them.</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="1DD04B7C" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="00C30BC2" w:rsidRDefault="00C30BC2" w:rsidP="00C30BC2"/><w:p w14:paraId="5AECA7D1" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="00C30BC2" w:rsidRDefault="00C30BC2" w:rsidP="00C30BC2"><w:r><w:t>* **Visualizations:**</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="43EED99D" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="00C30BC2" w:rsidRDefault="00C30BC2" w:rsidP="00C30BC2"><w:r><w:t xml:space="preserve">    1.  **Most Popular Genres (Word Cloud or </w:t></w:r><w:proofErr w:type="spellStart"/><w:r><w:t>Treemap</w:t></w:r><w:proofErr w:type="spellEnd"/><w:r><w:t>):** Based on the `</w:t></w:r><w:proofErr w:type="spellStart"/><w:r><w:t>listed_in</w:t></w:r><w:proofErr w:type="spellEnd"/><w:r><w:t>` column (split by comma). The size of the word/box represents the frequency of the genre (e.g., "International Movies", "Dramas", "Comedies").</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="3D1F29F6" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="00C30BC2" w:rsidRDefault="00C30BC2" w:rsidP="00C30BC2"><w:r><w:t xml:space="preserve">    2.  **Movie Duration Distribution (Histogram):** X-axis = `Movie Duration (Minutes)` grouped into bins (e.g., 0-60, 61-90, 91-120, 120+), Y-axis = Count of Movies.</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="6F99989B" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="00C30BC2" w:rsidRDefault="00C30BC2" w:rsidP="00C30BC2"><w:r><w:lastRenderedPageBreak/><w:t xml:space="preserve">    3.  **TV Show Seasons Distribution (Pie Chart or Donut Chart):** Breakdown of TV shows by number of seasons (1 Season, 2 Seasons, 3+ Seasons).</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="72807521" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="00C30BC2" w:rsidRDefault="00C30BC2" w:rsidP="00C30BC2"><w:r><w:t xml:space="preserve">    4.  **Top 10 Directors (Bar Chart):** Excluding "Unknown", show the directors with the most titles on the platform.</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="451A78E3" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="00C30BC2" w:rsidRDefault="00C30BC2" w:rsidP="00C30BC2"><w:r><w:t xml:space="preserve">    5.  **Top 15 Most Frequent Actors (Horizontal Bar Chart):** Based on the `cast` column (split by comma). Show which actors appear most frequently in the Netflix library.</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="239C66B9" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="00C30BC2" w:rsidRDefault="00C30BC2" w:rsidP="00C30BC2"/><w:p w14:paraId="421D7AE8" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="00C30BC2" w:rsidRDefault="00C30BC2" w:rsidP="00C30BC2"><w:r><w:t>**Styling &amp; Theming Guidelines:**</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="0000FCDD" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="00C30BC2" w:rsidRDefault="00C30BC2" w:rsidP="00C30BC2"><w:r><w:t>* **Theme:** Dark Mode (Background: `#141414`).</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="40F150F3" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="00C30BC2" w:rsidRDefault="00C30BC2" w:rsidP="00C30BC2"><w:r><w:t xml:space="preserve">* **Primary Accent </w:t></w:r><w:proofErr w:type="spellStart"/><w:r><w:t>Color</w:t></w:r><w:proofErr w:type="spellEnd"/><w:r><w:t>:** Netflix Red (`#E50914`).</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="04BB49A2" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="00C30BC2" w:rsidRDefault="00C30BC2" w:rsidP="00C30BC2"><w:r><w:t xml:space="preserve">* **Secondary </w:t></w:r><w:proofErr w:type="spellStart"/><w:r><w:t>Colors</w:t></w:r><w:proofErr w:type="spellEnd"/><w:r><w:t>:** White (`#FFFFFF`), Light Grey (`#B3B3B3`), and Dark Grey (`#333333`) for contrast.</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="2004748A" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="00C30BC2" w:rsidRDefault="00C30BC2" w:rsidP="00C30BC2"><w:r><w:t>* **Interactivity:** Enable tooltips on all charts so hovering reveals exact numbers and top titles associated with that data point. Enable cross-filtering (e.g., clicking on "India" in the map filters the Top Actors chart to only show actors in Indian content).</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="65F79DCF" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="00C30BC2" w:rsidRDefault="00C30BC2" w:rsidP="00C30BC2"/><w:p w14:paraId="676DF992" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="00C30BC2" w:rsidRDefault="00C30BC2" w:rsidP="00C30BC2"><w:r><w:t>***</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="010C3B0C" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="00C30BC2" w:rsidRDefault="00C30BC2" w:rsidP="00C30BC2"/><w:p w14:paraId="4D41E924" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="00C30BC2" w:rsidRDefault="00C30BC2" w:rsidP="00C30BC2"><w:r><w:t>### Why this structure works perfectly for your file:</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="7499E33E" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="00C30BC2" w:rsidRDefault="00C30BC2" w:rsidP="00C30BC2"><w:r><w:t>1. **It addresses the delimiters:** Your CSV has columns like `cast` and `</w:t></w:r><w:proofErr w:type="spellStart"/><w:r><w:t>listed_in</w:t></w:r><w:proofErr w:type="spellEnd"/><w:r><w:t xml:space="preserve">` where multiple names/genres are stuffed into one cell separated by commas. If the dashboard tool doesn't know to split them, it will treat "Comedies, Dramas" as </w:t></w:r><w:proofErr w:type="gramStart"/><w:r><w:t>a completely separate</w:t></w:r><w:proofErr w:type="gramEnd"/><w:r><w:t xml:space="preserve"> category from "Comedies". </w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="4EAFACAC" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="00C30BC2" w:rsidRDefault="00C30BC2" w:rsidP="00C30BC2"><w:r><w:t>2. **It separates the `duration` column:** Right now, your duration column has a mix of "90 min" and "1 Season". A dashboard cannot graph this on a single axis. The prompt explicitly instructs the tool to separate these into time (minutes) and count (seasons).</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w14:paraId="3C698BF0" w14:textId="448012BC" w:rsidR="001D54AF" w:rsidRPr="00C30BC2" w:rsidRDefault="00C30BC2" w:rsidP="00C30BC2"><w:r><w:t>3. **It handles the missing values:** Director and Cast columns have a lot of missing data (1,969 and 570 respectively). The prompt ensures these don't break your charts.</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:sectPr w:rsidR="001D54AF" w:rsidRPr="00C30BC2"><w:pgSz w:w="11906" w:h="16838"/><w:pgMar w:top="1440" w:right="1440" w:bottom="1440" w:left="1440" w:header="708" w:footer="708" w:gutter="0"/><w:cols w:space="708"/><w:docGrid w:linePitch="360"/></w:sectPr></w:body></w:document>